#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:8
msgid "Non-custodial node setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:10
msgid ""
"How to **relinquish control of a node's main account to an external "
"account**, so that the external account's private key is never required "
"in the node setup process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:12
msgid ""
"This is useful, for example, for service providers (also known as "
"*staking* service providers or *hosting* service providers) that work in "
"a **non-custodial** manner. This is, **customers** hire the **service "
"provider** to setup nodes for them and have any node rewards sent to "
"their main accounts, without ever sending their account keys to the "
"service provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:14
msgid ""
"This guide is intended for the service provider setting up a node on "
"behalf of their customer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:16
msgid ""
"There are **many mechanisms** to achieve this in |codename|. This page "
"explains the **simplest one**, assuming that the customer is not tech-"
"savvy (and therefore prefers not to use command-line tools like ``symbol-"
"cli``), and that **the customer's key are not allowed on an online "
"machine**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:19
msgid ""
"The process is even simpler if the customer's key are allowed to be "
"online."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:21
msgid "A guide will soon be added to this page describing this scenario."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:23
msgid ""
"**In summary**, once the node is completely setup, full control of the "
"node's **main account** will be transferred to the customer account "
"(called **external account**) by turning main into a :doc:`../../concepts"
"/multisig-account`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:25
msgid ""
"The service provider will prepare a transaction for offline signing and "
"send it to the customer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:26
msgid ""
"The customer signs the transaction using their Wallet from an offline "
"machine, and returns the signature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:27
msgid "The service provider announces the transaction."
msgstr ""

